      • createPopupMenu

        public static JPopupMenu createPopupMenu(ActionListener listener,
                                         Object... content)
                                  throws InvalidParameterException
        Create a contextual menu ready to use in some component. The menu will share the same listener for all options, whose functions will be defined by listener.
        Parameters:
        listener - The object that will listen to the menu items.
        content - The items to add.
        Returns:
        A JPopupMenu with all the items added and with the listener implemented.
        Throws:
        InvalidParameterException - In case any of the parameters is null.

      • createPopupMenu

        public static JPopupMenu createPopupMenu(ActionListener[] listeners,
                                         String[] content)
                                  throws InvalidParameterException
        Create a context menu ready to use in a component. Each option of the menu will have its own listener, so that each option performs a different function.
        Parameters:
        listeners - An array with all the listeners available.
        content - The items to add.
        Returns:
        A JPopupMenu with all the items added and with the listener implemented.
        Throws:
        InvalidParameterException - In case any of the parameters is null or listeners.length != content.length.

      • createPopupMenu

        public static JPopupMenu createPopupMenu(ActionListener listener,
                                         Object[] content,
                                         String[] commands)
                                  throws InvalidParameterException
        Create a context menu ready to use in a component. This menu will share the same listener for all the options, whose functions will be defined by listener and that will receive the commands defined in commands. You should be aware that if there is a sub-menu or a separator in content [i], then the value in commands [i] must be null.
        Parameters:
        listener - The object that will listen to the menu items.
        content - The items to add.
        commands - The available commands.
        Returns:
        A JPopupMenu with all the items added and with the listener and commands implemented.
        Throws:
        InvalidParameterException - In case any of the parameters is null or listeners.length != content.length.
        See Also:
        createPopupMenu(ActionListener, Object...), SEPARATOR
